This paper proposes a novel approach for predicting road traffic speed using spatio-temporal graph attention. The approach involves modeling dynamically changing spatial dependencies among roads and temporal patterns over long input sequences. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), social and information networks (cs.SI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Among these, machine learning (cs.LG) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new approach for traffic forecasting using attention mechanisms. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) are also likely categories as the paper involves modeling spatio-temporal dynamics in road networks. Social and information networks (cs.SI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) are less likely categories but still relevant as the paper involves modeling spatial dependencies and temporal patterns in traffic data.
